articles.title: Kaitlin Armstrong, convicted of killing Anna Moriah Wilson, sentenced to 90 years in prison - Austin American-Statesman
articles.description: A Travis County jury sentenced Kaitlin Armstrong on Friday to 90 years in prison for the fatal shooting of Anna Moriah Wilson on May 11, 2022, in East Austin.
articles.content:
A Travis County jury sentenced Kaitlin Armstrong on Friday to 90 years in prison for the fatal shooting of Anna Moriah "Mo" Wilson on May 11, 2022, in East Austin.
